      "text": [
        ": مَنِ اکْتَحَلَ بِمِیلٍ مِنْ مُسْکِرٍ کَحَلَهُ اللَّهُ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ بِمِیلٍ مِنْ نَارٍ قَالَ إِنَّ أَهْلَ الرِّیِّ فِی الدُّنْیَا مِنَ الْمُسْکِرِ یَمُوتُونَ عِطَاشاً وَ یُحْشَرُونَ عِطَاشاً وَ یَدْخُلُونَ النَّارَ عِطَاشاً."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "5. Abi (rah) from Muhammad b. Yahya from Muhammad b. Ahmad from Ya’qub b. Yazid from Marwak b. ’Ubayd from a man from Abi Abdillah (a.s.) that he said: “One who applies antimony containing alcohol in his eyes once, the Almighty Allah will rub a rod of fire in his eyes. People who drink wine in this world will die thirsty, will be assembled on the Day of Judgment thirsty and will be thrown into Hell thirsty.”"
        ]
      }
    },
